            <div class=3D"comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
               =20
                <span class=3D"comment-copy" itemprop=3D"text">What you hav=
e to remember when using FFTs is that there is an implicit periodicity in y=
our dataset with the supplied data pattern repeated in a cyclic loop. Your =
data is therefore equivalent to ...01234567012345670.... vs ...123456712345=
67... and numpy has done a radix 7 FFT here. Making an FFT deliver an accur=
ate DFT is distinctly non-trivial - people usually zero pad with almost as =
many zeroes as they have data and in addition apply a window function and/o=
r a compact convolution to the source data. Numerical Recipes isn't a bad p=
lace to look for some real world guidance on this.</span>
               =20
